Peste des petits ruminants,Tunisia
-----------------------------
Information received on 2 Aug 2012 from Dr Abdelhak Benyounes, Directeur general des services veterinaires, Ministere de l'agriculture et de l'environnement, Tunis, Tunisia

Summary
Report type Immediate notification
Start date 30 May 2012
Date of 1st confirmation of the event 17 Jul 2012
Report date 1 Aug 2012
Date submitted to OIE 2 Aug 2012
Reason for notification Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence 16 Apr 2012
Manifestation of disease Clinical disease
Causal agent Peste des petits ruminants virus
Nature of diagnosis Clinical, Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 Lessouda, Lessouda, Sidi Bouzid Est, Sidi Bouzid
Date of start of the outbreak 28 Jun 2012
Outbreak status Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit Farm
Affected animals
Species Susceptible Cases Deaths Destroyed Slaughtered
Sheep 289 7 4 0 0
Affected Population Sheep aged 3 to 12 months of Queue Fine de l'Ouest breed, owned by 2 farmers of the same region].

