Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[The map accompanying the OIE report depicts a fairly widespread outbreak, with cases ranging from Tunis to the middle of the country. It can also be seen on the ProMED HealthMap at the link below.

It is notable that there was an outbreak last March 2012 in adjacent Algeria, and we also report an outbreak in Egypt today (3 Aug 2012), see below. PPR continues to be a major challenge in the North African region, where sheep and goats are critically important. Efforts to control this outbreak should clearly be maximized given the stakes. - Mod.PC

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1Cft.]

[Photo of Queue Fine de l'Ouest (Western thin-tailed) breed of sheep:
http://www.vulgarisation.net/elevage/imageov/ovin9.jpg
- Mod.JW]

